caption: Good ramen.....great health precautions

Really really great place over all..service was 5 stars and the atmosphere was five stars. The gyoza was AMAZING!  Only reason this wasn't five stars was the flavor of the tonkotsu supreme wasn't ultimately there. Still really good.  But the tonkotsu wasn't Amazing. It was good but not Five stars amazing.
This is hands down the best ramen place!!! The food is delicious 🤤 We highly recommend 10/10. You will not be disappointed!!

I told my friends about this place with my highest recommendations. I visit this place often. This recommendation is always successful. The the cooking is appetizing and the crew is very friendly and cooperative. Whenever we visit this place we pass a gorgeous time.  highly recommended.
First time I had their turkey ramen. It made me nauseated. Second time I tried the shoyu, it's basically noodles soaked in soy sauce.
Never disappointing
Exceptional place to eat something when in a hurry. The customer service is fast, rates are fair, fantastic ambience. Highly recommended
I always go for the turkey miso! I have yet to try the other types of ramen but I love the shredded turkey with the miso broth!
The place offers a large range of fresh food. I love eating here. Staff members are always welcoming, rates are reasonable and the spot is always clean.
Best Ramen on the North side!

**Update: Management was super responsive regarding my experience, and I was so impressed by how professional and caring they were. I understand businesses have bad days, so I will continue to support them after seeing what this establishment is truly about.  I used to love Strings ramen before the pandemic, but a few months back I ordered my usual hell ramen for delivery, and it had hardly any flavor at all - just numbness from the peppercorn. I figured it was a fluke... then this time, I ordered the premium tonkotsu with hell sauce on the side. There was a lot of meat in bowl, but it tasted and smelled old. I ate it anyway, which was a big mistake because about 15 minutes after eating, I began to get extremely hot and get very nauseated. This morning I was sick again, and thank goodness I work remotely- otherwise I would’ve been out of work today.  After these two bad consecutive experiences, I don’t think I’ll be ordering from strings any more, especially considering with delivery costs, it’s about $32 for the meal...
Ramen, mmm, awesome. I look forward to a return visit. Prices were good for how much you get.
One of my top places for tasty ramen. Service is always prompt even when they have a full house. Menu is similar to a restaurant in El Paso I liked.
Great taste and reasonably priced.

(Translated by Google) Good taste. But bad service !!! The one that approached did not take care of us well 😡. I send someone else to take the order  (Original) Buen sabor. Pero mal servicio!!! La sta que se acercó no nos atendio bien 😡. Mando a alguien mas a que nos tomara la orden
Service was good. I had the pork don over rice and some pork gyozas. It was ok. I’ll be back to try the ramen for hopefully a better review!
Excellent location for delicious Ramen. i think i might become a regular. atmosphere is similar to a place in columbus i loved.

Flavorless ramen. Very occidental dish with no asiatic flavor, like a basic chicken broth with mushrooms. Looked more like a minestrone than ramen. Good point though: service is fast and tables are clean.

BEST RAMEN IN CHICAGO! My girlfriend and I are ramen fiends, get it at least once a week and we’ve been to furious spoon, nori, some places all around and nothing compares to strings here on Belmont !! Best broth and the most filling of noodles with solid meats and mushrooms ! Can’t praise this place enough !

I always come here for their pork gyoza and tonkotsu broth ramen. Their gyoza is nice and soft and the sauce they come in has a nice kick of spice. Their tonkotsu broth ramen is hearty and rich  and always fills me up nicely. I'm always excited to come back for more.
Came here because it says it’s dine-in is available. But only take out...
Good variety of ramen, and tasty broth. I'd go here again.
Super delicious food! Some of the best Ramen in Chicago.
Top level hell ramen is no joke.
One of my go to ramen spots in Chicago. Very quick and friendly service. Always has good music playing as well!

I'd say best ramen in Chicago. I've tried multiple spots and keep going back to Strings. Their noodles are probably the best with a good chewy bite. Broth is strong yet clean. I've done both indoor dining and delivery. They just started their ramen broth delivery in the last 2-3 months and I have to say that it does hold up extremely well. My go-tos are usually Tonkatsu with Kuro Buta and Maze Soba.
The food is consistently fresh and flavorful, workers provides fantastic customer service. I like how neat it is and atmosphere. I highly recommend this place.

Best Ramen in Chicago for your Ramen fix! Definitely way better than Furious Spoon down the block! Broth and noodles are richer and their vegetarian and vegan choices are also delicious! Their Sui Goza(dumplings) are super tasty, the Miso Premium is a must try, my favorite is the Tonkotsu Premium with lvl 4 sauce! Their Hell Ramen is no joke, but super tasty! If you think you can handle heat go for the 3, I’m still training my stomach to go for their Hell Ramen challenge!  China Town location has different menu(ramen dishes, yakisoba) but same great taste, when you get a chance try both! Separate review on their Google posting for recommendations!

Honestly the best ramen shop I've ever been to. And it's not just the food, but it's the staff as well. I'm an on and off regular because ramen is a treat for me, sometimes I spoil myself and eat here 3 times in a month, but no matter what my pattern may be or how much time has passed, I am always welcomed with the same vibe. The staff really takes time to remember their regulars, because as soon as I sit down the waiter or waitress will ask if I want my favorite drink that day. Service like this is hard to find, and again the food is absolutely amazing
Lot of premium ramen at a decent price. Serious spice!
Healthy, tasty, fast and always friendly people serving you. I come here for delicious healthy ramen and for the ambience as well.
Didn't take know what to expect, but they were BEYOND patient with me. Food was great.
Always delicious
It has the best noodles in town and the drinks are amazing I give them a five 5

Some of the best Ramen in Chicago. Quick service and friendly staff. Ordered takeout during "shelter and place" and was still great at home. Personal favorite is Tonkotsu Spicy Clams and Pork. Broth has just the right amount of kick.
People have criticized me for this but Strings is my favorite ramen spot. I live the tonkatsu and the chili oil.
The service and food are spectacular! The broth quality, as well as the menu selection are meticulously crafted. I enjoy the atmosphere and will always return.
I adore this restaurant very much. theres a special feeling. The cuisine is very tasty. the service is powerful and the team is well trained. The pay is satisfactory. deeply recommend.

As someone who's Japanese and had ramen all my life, this place is OKAY. I give a 4 star bc it's hard to find a good ramen place in Chicago. If you are used to okay ramen, I'd say this place is very good. I recommend Ramen Wasabi if you want authentic delicious ramen. Strings IS 300% better than Furious Spoon though. This place is a bit more expensive and is not as flavourful as other ramen places I know. The noodles are cooked too long and can get mushy. Soup/Broth isn't as rich as I wanted it to be. Cha-shu (braided pork) is tough and tastes okay. I'd not come back but I'd say it's worth going if you live nearby and are craving ramen.
Always done well with fast service. My favorite Ramen in the city

Had the ramen with pork belly, actually very tasty, freshly prepared.  You could tell the broth wasn't from a can or pre-made. I also could see the cooks in the kitchen working vigorously to get the meals ready asap!  My only complaint was the restaurant is kind of uncomfortable, they don't have any cushions on the seats.  Ouch!
This place always delivers. They serve great dishes for fair rates, there no long wait even when the place is packed.
Such good ramen

One of my friends is always posting about going out for ramen, so I finally asked her to take me. Strings is her favorite so we came here. First of all, it's BYOB which is nice, and my friend brought a 6 pack of beer to share. One of my criteria for any restaurant is that they have to have a vegetarian option for me, and luckily Strings has several. I ordered the Kinoko Shoyu ramen and it was delicious. There was a sweetness to it that I finally attributed to the mascarpone cheese. All in all, it was yummy and I would go back in a heartbeat.
A bit pricey but AWESOME broth, noodles, meat.  Have ramen as hot as you like. Tonkatsu premium better than premium!!!!
Big portion delusions))!

This is unquestionably our favorite restaurant to go to as a family. My boys love the kids miso ramen and edamame. I am always torn between their Hell Ramen and Maze Soba with pork. So good! Excellent atmosphere, and we have always had excellent costumer service every time we come. Thank you!
Awesome food every time I’ve been in. One of the better spots in the city

Ramen was delicious, with quick service. This place can get very crowded, and would recommend trying it for lunch to beat some of the crowds! Will be returning to try their level 5 hell ramen next time I am in Chicago!
The noodles are too firm. Almost like angel hair pasta instead of ramen noodles. The tonkotsu broth isn't creamy enough, a bit too watery. Tastes a lot better after level 1 hell spice at least.

Edited review: I decided to edit my review after management reached out to me after our first experience here. We gave Strings another chance and did not regret it. We ordered the same Tonkotsu Ramen that we ordered the first time and even had some Tiramisu for our dessert, which was very delicious. I'm glad management was so kind to reach out to us. We'll definitely be visiting Strings again in the future. :)  Original review: We actually loved the ramen and thought the service was great. We both ordered the Tonkotsu with Pork Belly. Unfortunately, we got food poisoning from eating here. We won't be returning.
Broth 12/10, noodles 7/10,  porkbelly 8/10, service 9/10
Limited seating space but friendly staff and good food.

I really enjoyed it. Ramen was delicious, you can add a half or full order of extra noodles. Also, I liked the atmosphere, which has more of a classic ramen shop vibe as opposed to a regular restaurant that serves ramen.
Has great ramen. I cant stop eating it.
This.place is reqlly.popular so if you want to come on Friday make sure to be there before 5 pm otherwise theres a waiting list. The food is phenomenal!

Customer service was absolutely horrible. Being my first time there, I asked a couple of questions about the food, bought a bowl of ramen and had a cherry blossom soda. In the middle of me enjoying my food the police comes into the restaurant saying that I was reported as a disturbance. I was removed from the restaurant. If that's not discrimination, I don't know what is. Once I exited in all the confusion. I misplaced my debit-card so I stayed around to look for it. I also had to check my bank account to make sure I wasn't scammed. If that small space by the soda was an employee only area nobody told me. By the way I wasn't  intoxicated. They were nervous of me as soon as I sat down to eat. Why was my order taken and why did they take my money?
My favorite ramen restaurant in Chicago. It's also in a convenient location right off of the Red Line!
This place simply knows how to please their customers. Regularly with a nice attitude. The food is reasonably priced, constantly flavorful and clean.
Good ramen. Great spicey Hell ramen 🤘🔥 Get it hot! Only way to go.
Breath taking ramen. Strings, I simply love you.
Try the hell ramen
Menu isn't as robust as the Chinatown location, but their ramen is still as good.
Friendly and helpful waiting staff and great ramen.
Went there on a recommendation, now I've added it to my favorite places.  Great broth and noodles making a can't miss base.
Ramen is so good! Excellent service and vrry friendly! Definitely recommend this place if you're up for some yummy food!
I constantly come getting some food here. I enjoyed the rapid service and well prepared food. Keep up the good work.
Best food, very friendly staff, constantly excellent mood. They charge reasonable rates and the food quality is very good. Keep it up.
This is my favorite ramen place in Chicago. It's small but I have never had to wait for a table. The ramen always makes it to my table shortly after ordering.
The food quality and customer service has always been great. A great bowl of Ramen is comforting at any time, especially when it is really cold outside!
Always delicious

Got a pretty sick after the meal here. I have edited this review because the management was very responsive and kind in light of what happened. They reconciled the issue well. The ramen is ok, not a bad stop. The service is really great. I'm sure it was a rare issue for them.  Hello Alec!  Once again our apologies for a bad experience at Strings. We are very serious when it comes to our customers health and comfort. The kitchen has been informed about the incident, chef will personally check every produce and have a sanitation meeting with the staff. Severs are reminded of allergy and food intolerance questions while taking the order, that is part of our policy. Meanwhile we would like to compensate you with a free ramen dinner gift card you can redeem at any Strings location. Please provide best address we can mail it to.  We hope your next experience at Strings will be amazing!  Thank you! Strings Management
Quaint little noodle bar. Pleasant staff and good food. Not my favorite ramen place but that could change on subsequent visits.

Excellent service and wonderful food. The level 2 hell ramen was exactly what we needed on a cold January evening. The pork gyozas were great as well. If we see any other shows nearby, Strings is top of the list. Some of the best ramen we've had in Chicago.

Took my family of 5 there after seeing a nearby show based on reviews of area restaurants on google maps.  Most restaurants were almost empty - there was a 40 minute wait here (they send you a text and you can monitor your place in line on your phone).  Plenty of interesting shops in the area to explore while waiting.  Our first time here (and at a ramen noodle place), we asked for recommendations.  My youngest was happy with the kids Ramen bowl with potstickers.  The rest of us went with either the Miso or Tonkotsu ramen.  Everyone was very happy with their choices, with a couple needing to take leftovers home.  Service was excellent.
Really good food and very cute vibe. Will definitely be back.
Really liked the spicy level 3 ramen
Was good.  Presentation and amount of vegetables were lacking. Service was great.
Excellent service from a knowledgeable server with great food

I got the miso ramen with pork belly. It came with bamboo shoots, corn, nori and bean sprouts. The broth was very flavorful, just the right amount of seasoning. If you like it spicy, they had chilli oil and chilli powder on the table so you can adjust your broth to your level of spiciness. Would definitely go back. The only thing I was a little disappointed in was the portion for the noodles. I finished my noodles, but I still had so much broth left and no noodles to eat it with.

I love a good bowl of ramen. I got the tonkotsu with pork belly and level 3 death sauce on the side. I ended up using the entire side of death sauce and was very content. I'd say the spice level was right where I hoped it would be, 6 out 10 spicys. I hope to come back and work up to level 4 death ramen!  A good note, this place is BYOB, so I went to Target across the street and brought a six pack beforehand! The staff was also great. I had Ceaser as my server who was really kind and made good conversation.  Will be back for more death ramen!

Had the ramen with the filet mignon, and I can easily say this was the best ramen I have ever had. The broth was flavorful, there was the perfect amount of seasoning and heat, and there were plenty of noodles and meat, unlike some ramen places I’ve been to. Definitely going again!
Good ramen. Quick service. Close to trsnsit at Belmont L station. The hell ramen at the lowest level is just very slightly spicy. If you want heat you probably have to go to level 3.
Ramen bowls,  awesome. Great tasting food. Small place so you may have a wait. Loved the Hell Ramen. Highly recommended.
This is our go to ramen place ANYWHERE in the Chicagoland area. Been to the others but this one keeps drawing back as they’re always consistent and delicious!

Super delicious ramen and love the sashimi bowls! Extremely fast customer service and got meal within minutes. Loved the flavors of the ramen and how they have a hell challenge where you can win $50 if you can handle super spicy food!
Absolutely delicious!
Katie Dong's recipes are to die for.
Amazing food!!!! Fair prices
Quick in and out. Ordered the turkey ramen (it's November now, so...) Didn't have an egg, but still good. Service was fast.
Chicago definitely has some great ramen and Strings ramen shop is one of them! Located in a chill neighborhood, it's worth the wait!
Great ramen! Buta Pork Belly Tonkotsu Ramen was delicious, the portions are really generous, I hardly finished mine.
Staff was very quick, kind, and attentive. The shop is small but lively. The ramen was just okay. The broth was a little too watery and the noodles were kind of bland. A little bit on the pricey side
The best vegetarian ramen I've had in Chicago!
First ramen I had in the city 5 years ago. And still coming back for more! It's my favorite!
Get the lvl 5 hell ramen
Great atmosphere, authentic flavors, and wonderful service!!!

Amazing experience everytime. Awesome vibe and music. Phenomenal ramen. Try the  lower levels of Hell Ramen. Or if dare..sign the waiver and do the Level 5, but only if you are a ghost and scorpion pepper pro.
It's open late, and the ramen is tasty, though not the best I've had.
Best ramen I've had so far.
Great place! Very accommodating hip place. Amazing food. They are truely interested in making sure you love it

Pretty expensive, but I've never experienced legit ramen, so it was great to try it out finally. Waitstaff there are very friendly and know the menu back to back with ease. I had the lvl 3 Ramen and my partner had the creamy pork ramen.

Wonderful little ramen place in Lakeview! The servers were so helpful explaining the menu to us and provided great service. The ramen was AMAZING as were the pork gyoza dumplings!!!! My ramen had fresh ramen noodles, a flavorful broth, a fatty pork belly and scallions. It's a casual spot but great for lunch or dinner!
Ramen here is clearly made with love and has a perfect chill atmosphere

I had met a friend in the area and we were looking for a good place to eat, saw this and decided to try it. I had the Shoyu Ramen (I think that's how you spell it) for the first time and it was AMAZING! Didn't know what to expect but both my friend and I were pleasantly surprised. I would definitely recommend to anyone looking for a good ramen spot.
Amazing Ramen noodles soup.
The ramen is delicious, and they have vegan options! The staff is always friendly, welcoming, and knowledgable. Ask them anything about the food- they'll know the answer!
I'm not Strings Ramen Shop Lakeview but this place is bomb, the waitress Ashley was super nice and accommodating and explained the menu to us, great place!

The miso ramen, i think is good, it’s your first time to try the plates are expensive in my opinion, i spend 42 dollars the place are beautiful, if you want to sit, you need to wait 10 minute, service is very polite. the dessert is wonderful.

I honestly have no idea what I ate... I waited until my husband ordered and pulled the "I'll have exactly what he's having!" Card.  Anyways, there was like steak fillets in the bowl and it was very tender and very tasty. The tables are super small, we went there with 5 people and felt very crowded around the table. The service was really great and professional.  I went in the dead of summer and still enjoyed it.

Awesome restaurant. Best ramen of the 5 places I’ve tried, big spice range, nice atmosphere, only complaint is it’s kinda small and can get busy, but that’s common for most great restaurants. Great service when you sit down, and seriously delicious food, and open late which is the best
Best Ramen in Chicago. Fight me.
Hell Ramen is my fave, the broth is super tasty and the toppings complement it very well.
Nice place, delicious ramen!
Very good flavor and filling, noodles were perfectly cooked
Excellent service...nice people nice place....recommended
Really great service, nicely paired with awesome Ramen.  I’m a bit of a lightweight and tried Level 1 Hell Ramen...but I will be back for the rest of them!
Pog

I had a dag gum experience.  I got the exact right level of spicy (which for me was level 3). And not only did I enjoy all the flavor in my bowl, but also a wonderful kind of spice high.  I feel like I wouldn't enjoy the flavors as much at level 4, but I'd really like to try it.  Definitely recommend adding an egg.
Bro...yes
Better than furious spoon
Excellent customer service. Great music. Awesome ramen!
Decent ramen for a decent price with cool vibes. Would want to try the hell challenge sometime.
Good ramen, though not as good as Oiistar. Menu is also a little confusing.
loved this place! delicious food and great service
Really good vegetarian, spicy ramen! Nice casual atmosphere, and interior design.
Open late during the week, and the food never disappoints no matter what time of day you go. Tons of food so you will never leave hungry.
Food was mediocre.  Have had better ramen elsewhere.
A very cozy place and a relax atmosphere

Best authentic house-made ramen noodles in the area that we’ve found. The menu is limited so food comes out pretty fast and you aren’t overwhelmed by too many options. We love this because we always get the same things. We go so regularly that our favorite server knows what we are going to order. My favorite is the shoyu prime ramen. The steak is thin-sliced and high quality. Broth is flavorful and not overly salty as is common in chain shops. I don’t like the bamboo but my partner does so I just pop those into her bowl. She prefers the shoyu kinoko (mushroom) ramen. And we usually get the wasabi string beans as an appetizer. Sometimes we order extra noodles (kae dama) or try the newest dessert. They can get pretty busy at times and there can be a bit of a wait. I wouldn’t go with more than 4 people as it’s a pretty small space. We love Strings and hope you will love it too!!

Great Japanese restaurant. I had the miso salmon sunomono and it was great. Very light and fresh. My wife had the hell ramen level 1 and she enjoyed that as well. Highly recommend this place. Good service, great vibe!
ramen and service here is quality. Cool location to meet with coworkers. Quick, helpful, and friendly service. The place has a good atmosphere.

Great ramen spot with homemade noodles, big portions, and quick and attentive service. The Hell Ramen challenge (Level 5) is by far the spiciest dish I've ever tried. Level 3 and below are not bad if you like spicy food. I would highly recommend Strings over the other nearby ramen places
Food is great and service is quick. Vegan miso ramen is flavorful and not too heavy.
Delicious and fun!
So good.
Good stock and fixings! Had the shoyu with onsen egg and pork loin. Just wish their egg noodles were a little finer and crinklier but that may be personal preference. Also fyi it's BYOB.
Best ramen ever! Dumplings were amazing too!

I received excellent service this Wednesday afternoon from a server who recommended to me the spicy clam & pork tonkatzu ramen for my lunch today. It was at a light to medium spice level, appropriate probably for most diners, even on a warm summerlike day like today. I got stuck in a rut of continuously ordering pork belly and was finally ready to try something different. This really hit the spot and I’ll definitely be coming back!! And thank you for the recommendation.
Best ramen in Chicago for vegetarians.
I come here alone too much, but it's worth sitting down to a quality bowl of ramen.
The best Ramen shop EVER. Anytime I'm craving Ramen, I come here. It's just sooo good 😩😩
Delicious!
Great food! Great service!
I have yet to find an item on the menu that I haven't truly enjoyed. The Shoyu, Tonkotsu and Miso ramen bowls are all fantastic. The value for money and service are both great.
This is my favorite ramen shop. The end!
Better than Furious Spoon

Strings Lakeview is decent and consistent with the flavor but, their Chinatown location is the superior location. I enjoyed the convenience of an authentic ramen shop in the north side but as most places it can get a little Americanized. If you are someone with more sensitive taste buds or want to treat your out of town parents take them here. If you’re adventurous and enjoy intense flavor profiles the Chinatown location is the one to try. The flavor is definitely on the more American and dull side these days.
My favorite ramen place in Chicago! Love the Hell ramen!

Excellent ramen choice. Best shoyu ramen in town. Must try pork belly shoyu ramen. I love spicy levels 3. Spicy and hot but not overpowering. This location serving gyoza in sauce. Love it. Street parking and hard to find.
Best ramen in Chicago

I've been here 2-3 times and every time I go there the waiters were exceptionally nice to me. I've been to a lot of ramen shops and by far this place treats you like family rather than a customer. The atmosphere and decor of this shop feel warm and inviting. However, I've tried many iterations of a shoyu ramen and unfortunately, this shop's version isn't my favorite. It's an acquired taste and personally, I don't yet have the pallet for their shoyu ramen. A lot of ramen shops I visited will usually have a picture in their menu or an oversimplified ingredient list so that newcomers will know what they're getting. This shop doesn't have pictures but does list out the ingredients however they do it in a way that was jarring to me where the menu had a footnote explaining in further detail the ingredients. I would like to think that this shop isn't intentionally trying to confuse their guest but rather try to establish a level of authenticity that I, while it seems I'm critical of, thoroughly enjoy because it adds to the overall dining experience. Overall I liked coming to this shop and it will be in my list of ramen shops that would recommend people to visit.
Excellent broth
Fantastic
Really good Miso. Cool venue. Could have had a little more flavor. However, you could always put red pepper on it made it more flavorful.
Level 3 house flavor all the way.

This is the third it forth time I've gone here. And everything is great about this place. The food the atmosphere. It's awesome. There's also a cool bookstore and retro store right next to it. Good place to eat and hang out. I'd go any day.
Great vegan options!
This place is close by..i like the ramen..but i do see a slight difference in the broth between their Chinatown branch and the Belmont one...i wonder if everyone feels the same
Delicious ramen noodle soup; had the vegetarian version, tasty. The service was very good and staff attentive.  The place is the new dining  hotspot in Lakeview.
Very friendly staffs and tasty Japanese style noodle.

First visit at this Ramen place, it’s very cramped and gets crowded specially on Friday nights. It’s a tight spaced restaurant with good quality ramen. I’ve tried their other branch in Chinatown which has similar layout and place gets really packed and busy! I love that noodles are not from packet some restaurant serves noodles from packet.. prices have change from my previous visit or probably because this one is near Lakeview, flavors were delicious it wasn’t too salty but I love the right amount of heat. Noticeably smaller portions on toppings which is sad. But the staff was overall helpful and accommodating! Still one of the best in Chicago!
Excellent Ramen!
The staff are very helpful with explaining menu items and the food is excellent.
Soups were pretty good but noodles not much
The gyudon is great. Wish they had it at the Chinatown location
Delicious

Flipping amazing!!!! Server was nice. The restaurant was clean. But back to the food, AMAZING. I love spicy, so seeing the different levels you could try pulled me in right away. RECOMMENDED FOR ALL. verteran ramen eaters and novices like myself. I WILL BE BACK
One of the best ramens I have tried it here. 😋

Decent ramen got a mix of beef clam and another meat think it was called the delux? The spice level was perfect, there, but not blow your socks off hot (they offer that too, there is a range of heat available which I love). They have a turkey ramen for those with limited meat options. The waiter was informative and helpful and service was fast the way ramen should be, easy!

The food was ok, except one girl made us feel like we were a problem, just because we didn't want to sit by the door she practically ignored us and had someone else check on us, short Asian girl. Good luck in a busy night the space is pretty tight with everyones coats in the way, no coat hanger BTW.

Quite a bit expensive for the portion they serve, but the quality is good. Even though the taste is different from the original ramen served in Japan, I think it has been well adopted to serve American taste. Lots of options offered in terms of spice level, and I loved the boiled egg served with ramen.
😍😍😍 love it very friendly and clean
Great ramen and ambience. Try the tree mushrooms. It's BYOB.
It was ok. Def not the best ramen out there

Strings is definitely one of our all-time favorite restaurants.  ALL of the ramen is excellent and we also love the maze soba.  It's very hard to go wrong here if you like savory dishes.   The prices are fair given the big, high quality meal, and there are good, inexpensive side dish options too.  Seating is a little tight so small groups are best here (I wouldn't go more than 6 people).  You get your food pretty fast so it's a great place to stop in and go if you're in a hurry.
Strings has decently good ramen but the pricing is a little on the higher side.

Love the 5 different levels of the ramen they have to offer. Depending on your spice appetite would urge to anywhere between 1 through 3. Seems to me like level 5 should more or less feel like hot oil being poured down your throat. But sure did enjoy BYOB to wash it down.
I can keep eating this everyday

Great noodle place. I'd say it ranks average in my scale of delicious ramen. Pretty fast but the wait times are a bit annoying at this location. This shop is designed to get you in and out. Probably wouldn't linger long here.
Great ramen. Come early. It's a small space and gets busy at dinner.
Very tasty soups. I loved the shrimp dumpling appetizer. Super fast service.
I've never had ramen so fantastic in my life

My chicken gyoza was SO good, so, so good! Love the spicy sauce that it comes with as well. I didn't get the ramen since I wasn't too hungry, just needed a late night snack.. But I did taste some of my friend's ramen and boy, was it good!
Excellent ramen varieties and friendly service, but dropping 2 stars as they do not serve ramen to go.
Cannot judge how authentic Japanese they are, but the spicy-clam/pork ramen was overall very good.
Solid, broth better than noodles, noodles need more bounce.

I've had ramen in Japan & this is one of the best I've had (despite the mix up), with vegan options to boot! Strings Ramen Chinatown opened years ago, but I never stopped by since friends didn't like it & online reviewers concurred. But I'm glad I was in the area today because it was hands down one of the top 3 ramen I've had. After many mediocre bowls of ramen in Japan, I learned I don't like traditional soup ramen, so I got the Vegan Sesame Mazemen ($13) & everyone at my table wanted a bite. However, I told my waitress I'm vegan & it still came with an egg on top :( I didn't make a big deal out of it since we were in a hurry. We also got the lunch special Pork Curry Rice (very tasty) & the Pork Belly Don (AMAZING VALUE for $12). The service was fast, wait staff nice. 100% my new favorite ramen in Chicago.

Always a pleasure to eat ramen from Strings Ramen Shop! Some of the best in the city. The noodles aren't slimy and mushy, a wide selection of broths and styles, BYOB! The list goes on and on. Would highly recommend to anyone in the area. Definitely better that other Lakeview Ramen Shops.
Best ramen in the city!

Today I went out with my boyfriend to strings as we usually do when we crave ramen. I had the shoyu (I'm sorry I may have misspelled it) prime ramen he had the level 3 spicy ramen. Here is what I love about this place. They have four options on how you want your ramen. Light, medium, heavy, and spicy. This is the best way to describe the four style because they leave you feeling like this, and all of them taste amazing. I'm so happy that we have found this amazing place and love visiting here when the mood strikes.
Their hellfire ramen is legit spicy! Oh, and their tonkatsu ramen is delicious too.
The ramen was pretty good, but I think it was kind of expensive. The broth wasn’t my favorite, but I’d be interested to go back and try the miso ramen.
Excellent food! Make sure to get the belly pork
Best ramen in the neighborhood!
Good service, delicious food, and they don't mess around when they say something is spicy.  It would be nice if the restaurant was ADA compliant, but that's more of a building owner issue.

The most amazing ramen. I got the vegetarian spicy level 2 ramen, Hands down the best thing I have ever tasted!! Went here for my birthday with my family of 8 and we all loved our ramen. Staff was so kind too ❤️

Good ramen, it's fairly authentic compared to what I had in Japan. The tonkatsu is good and has a little spice. The hell ramen is a mix between Japanese ramen and a Chinese hot pot. Good if you like your food really spicy.
Great tasting ramen! Loved the atmosphere too.

The food here is both delicious and visually appealing. I've been here a few times for the ramen. I ordered the creamy ramen and made it spicy. I'm happy to say the broth had a nice rich complex flavor profile with quality noodles. In the broth you will find plenty of fresh vegetables and a delicious lava egg. The price for their ramen is between $15 and $19, which is about the same as the other ramen restaurants I've been to. The restaurant is very small, but is clean and has a nice vibe. The servers are active and greet everyone who walks in the door. Great place overall.

Probably the definitive ramen shop in Chicago. The one on Belmont is almost identical to the classic spot in Chinatown, with coxy seating for small parties and walk ins. The menu isnt too complex or varied, but thats a plus as it focuses on the key thing: ramen.  Get the tonkatsu for a creamy, savory bowl of heaven (go for pork belly, not loin) or go with the HELL ramen for a spicy, incredible experience

Best Ramen in the area!! I LOVED THIS PLACE. I literally walked by this place for months wanting to stop since its always busy. Finally got a chance to stop in and it was well worth it. Loved the atmosphere of the place and the food was on point.
Extra side of home made noodles for all the sexy broth. Definitely coming back
love strings good ramen I would recommend it.
Great place to go on a cold Chicago day to warm up. Their ramen was delicious, and the service was fantastic.
Absolutely delicious ramen and really quick service. Also, kudos to whoever picks the music!!
Ramen on point
Hearty bowl. Right amount of spicy. Doesnt deserve to be Hell Noodles though, unless you get the 4 or the 5 defcon, like the table nearby. They were in tears. 😲😲😲😲😝 You were warned by your server.
The best....
Good flavor in the ramen but way more oily than what I'm used to so I wasn't able to eat the whole thing.

As some of the reviews below indicated, terrible place to go as a vegan. Overpriced, largely tasteless, small portion and barely any toppings or noodles. And on top of that you pay extra and some off menu cost? No thanks-- can find better ramen places in Chicago.

Total waste of time. Rude staff. Not vegan friendly. I went in to get the only vegan option they had which was vegan noodles. They refused to sell me vegan noodles to go!!! Are you serious!!! I'm on my lunch break do I have to sit there and eat to be able to get food? RIDICULOUS!! And to top it all off the person I was talking to showed me the carry out menu (so stupid) and I asked ok what's vegan in here? And she totally ignored my question. What a joke of a place that tries to attract vegans with a dish that they refuse to sell you unlessyou eat it there... What kind of nonsense is that???? So frustrating
The ramen that doesn't burn your stomach has better broth

Went last night and again today, I got the lowest spice option, don't remember the name sorry, it was awesome! had like a sichuan flavour to it and the noodles were well cooked with a hearty amount of veggies and other adornments, they're shoyu based ramen is bomb too, polite servers and i was given a table even though i showed up like 30 mins before closing
Great Turkey miso ramen and very fast for lunch.

Great ramen, a little pricey, but I'd go back because it's tasty. Located on Belmont so parking can be tricky. Service is good and they menu has pretty much anything you'd expect or want from a ramen shop.
Like a  Massage for the Seoul
Delicious Ramen. I ordered Shoyu with Prime (strips of fillet mignon). It tasted great but it came with very little steak.
My favorite ramen in Chicago two years running
Some great choices here. The spice is well tempered and the broth isn't overly salty like some other places. Purchase the additional egg, it's well worth it
The flavor and service was great.
I've had better ramen in the city, but this wasn't bad.  A little pricey at $18 a bowl, and I didn't really care for their hot pepper concoction.
Great ramen! Great service

Strings is, in my opinion, one of the better ramen chains in Chicago. I feel like other shops don't properly cook their noodles or their broth is a little bit less flavorful than I would like. Mushy noodles is the worst though. I ordered the level 3 spicy ramen and I think it was well balanced. Portion size is normal. Both Strings locations I've visited have incredibly similar decor, almost identical, and quality seems consist between them.
Noodles is good, soup is okay.
my favorite ramen in the city. do the hell challenge if you can handle spicy.
Def one of the top ramen places I've eaten at. Good fast service and delicious food. Gyoza was fantastic!
Ramen connoisseur, just found my new favorite!
They can make some decent vegan ramen. Not the best I've ever had though
best ramen i have experienced!
Next to their Chinatown location, this ones just as good!
Decent
Reallllllly good. Will go again if ever in the area.
Awesome
Great ramen! Small, cozy spot. The service was great too!
Good but still not as good as the original

This place was soooooooo good! We went at 8pm for dinner on a Thursday and it was busy but we were seated immediately. The service was great and we got our food super fast. Spicy menma appetizer was great. The flavor of the shiyo ramen was superb. My level 2 hell ramen had the perfect level of spice for me; the flavor of the spices blended deliciously with the other flavors, and the spiciness was present but not overpowering. I love ramen and I'll definitely be back here!

The food is excellent, the staff responsive. The price point is on the high end for what it serves, and there was something off with the facilities, like it wasn't as well maintained as it should be in a strange way.

We really enjoyed our experience here! The customer service was excellent and the quality of the food was exceptional. Our order consisted of a Hell Ramen Level 2 with a side of Hell Sauce Level 3 and a Tonkatsu with a side of Hell Sauce Level 2. Flavors of each dish were accurately described in the menu, as well by the wait staff whom draw caution upon ordering higher level tiers.

OVER priced, small portion, noodle was Chewy in the end, walked out hungry.....
Good ramen with a good atmosphere.
One of my favorite places in all of Chicago, I come here all the time. It would be a great place to bring a date, the staff is friendly, helpful and always attentive. Visit if you can!
Friendly servers and really good ramen; wait staff are willing to help brave souls trying to work their way up the tiers of hell ramen

The Hell Ramen is amazing!! As a spice lover, it's hard to find a balance between heat and flavor but this dish masters both. I'm currently on level 4 or 5 which has ghost pepper in it. I like to think I'm "training" for the level 5 …
Good food, but it's a little cramped
Great ramen!
Hell Ramen Level 2!
Excellent ramen, and a couple (just a few) options for non ramen folks too. To them, I recommend the gyu don. Really good.
Great food, great service!!!
Supreme

I LOVE STRINGS! Honestly I could eat here everyday, I am never disappointed. Level 1 or 2 ramen is my top picks and the shrimp gyoza is where it's at. I remember this spot used to be Ramen-ster like a year or two ago and it was ok, but Strings definitely outshines it. I would definitely recommend this place without hesitation.
Good price and good food in a cute place.
As a vegitarian, I found the food very good.  I would go back.
So good.
